                      Bridal fashion fiesta                    The wedding fashion industry in India has changed greatly over the last decade or so. As brides of the 21st century no longer want to cling to the traditional attire worn by earlier generations, the occasion now calls for a display of sartorial style and elegance of the highest order. Tonights fashion show, KKN Group of Companies presents Marriage n Vogue at The Telegraph Weddings 2010, in association with Seagrams Blenders Pride, the fourth edition of The Telegraph Weddings and the third of Marriage n Vogue, offers a splendid survey of modern tastes and trends in wedding fashion in the country. Featuring Bollywoods favourite designer Manish Malhotra and veteran city designer duo Mona and Pali, it will bring together some of the biggest names to walk the ramps today. Alicia Raut, Candice Pinto and Nethra Raguraman lead the list of catwalkers along with their male counterparts Asif Azim and Freddy Daruwala. While Malhotra will showcase a line in which tradition meets the trend, Monapali explores the theme of return to nature with their organic and ethnic creations. Choreographed by Lubna Adam.                    Event: A fashion show on wedding apparel When: Today; 8.30 pm onwards Where: The Pala, ITC The Sonar	                    
